  <a href="https://media.licdn.com/mpr/mpr/AAEAAQAAAAAAAAO4AAAAJDFkMjA5OWI3LTE3MmUtNGIyMC1iZTVkLTNjZDc1ODYzM2I1NA.jpg" style="color: #b4445c; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;">
    <img alt="books, books, books" border="0" height="267" src="https://cdn.finotto.org/uploads/2015/10/27022226/read-more-cover-1100x733.jpg" title="Source: Michele Finotto" width="400" />
  </a>
</div>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: center;">
  <i>
    "What we really need is not more authors,<br />
    or better publishers.<br />
    What we most need is<br />
    a vastly better system<br />
    to identify the books we will love."
  </i>
  
  <br />

  <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2016/01/16/book-it-baby/" style="color: #b4445c;" target="_blank">
    <span style="font-size: medium;"><b>TechCrunch</b></span>
  </a>
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  Beantown Web has developed such a system. For the ninth year running Beantown Web has conducted a quasi-scientific meta-search to identify the best business books published during the calendar year. These books are most likely to add value to your career.
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  This year's search began by identifying 11 "Best of" lists. This resource list is available upon request. Presented here are the results.
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  A total of 110 books were mentioned on at least one "Best of" list — 77 of these books were mentioned only once.
</p>

<h3 style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;">
  The Honorable Mention Shelf
</h3>
  
<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  An additional 15 books were mentioned on two lists and these books comprise the <b>Honorable Mention</b> list.
</p>

